  "prompt": "Is alcohol allowed while traveling in Indian Railways?",
  "response": "Yes, passengers are generally allowed to carry alcohol when traveling on Indian Railways, but there are a few important points to consider:\n\n1. **Consumption on Trains**: While carrying alcohol is allowed, consumption of alcohol is prohibited in the general compartments of Indian Railways. Passengers are allowed to consume it in designated areas, such as in private compartments or in certain classes of travel (like first class).\n\n2. **State Regulations**: The rules about carrying alcohol may vary depending on the state you are traveling through, as some states in India have strict regulations on the sale and consumption of alcohol. It\u2019s important to check the regulations of the states along your route.\n\n3. **Quantity Limits**: There may be restrictions on the quantity of alcohol a passenger can carry. It's advisable to carry reasonable amounts for personal consumption.\n\n4. **Waiters and Catering**: In certain premium trains, like the Rajdhani or Shatabdi Express, passengers may be able to order alcoholic beverages through the onboard catering service, where available.\n\nAlways check the specific guidelines or inquire with Indian Railways before your travel for any recent changes or additional restrictions.",
